    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An aromatic liquid phenol, isoeugenol is a constituent of the essential oils of several plants including nutmeg. It may also be synthesized from closely related eugenol by isomerization with alkali. Isoeugenol is used in perfumery and in the synthesis of vanillin. </Note_Text>
